  "text": "In table 2 we summarize the main instantiations of NTRU 3 (for further details the reader is referred to [CITATION_1] Section 2] ). Sometimes, for efficiency reasons, a combination of the above sets might be used. For example in NTRU-2001 q might be a prime or in NTRU-2005 L r and F might belong in X (d) which denotes the set of (binary) polynomials of the from b 1 + b 2 * b 3 where b i are very sparse binary polynomials with d 1s. ",
